<TITLE> DSE turnover crosses Tk 1.0bn mark </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jun 3 (bdnews24.com) - Turnover on the Dhaka Stock Exchange crossed Tk 1.0 billion mark in midday trade Sunday amid heavy buying into the shares of banks and power companies. Power Grid Company of Bangladesh led the market. "Price level and transactions appear to be good. Let's see how the market behaves in the remaining session," said Salahuddin Ahmed Khan, chief executive of the DSE. At 11.43am, the DGEN or general index added 6.62 points or 0.33 percent to 2010.21. The DSI or all-share price index gained 6.14 points or 0.37 percent to 1664.5. Turnover reached Tk 1.15 billion in midday trade. Total turnover was Tk 1.70 billion Thursday. Of the issues traded on the DSE, 85 advanced, 48 fell and nine held steady. Power Grid Company of Bangladesh, BRAC Bank, Prime Bank, Southeast Bank and Square Pharma were top issues in turnover by 11.28am. Power Grid grew to Tk 620 from Thursday's close at Tk 590.75 on anticipation of higher return after the power sector got 16 percent allocation in the annual development programme for fiscal 2007-08. BRAC Bank fell to Tk 703.25 from Tk 783.5. Prime Bank dropped to Tk 820 from Tk 832.5 due to profit-taking. Southeast Bank also dipped to Tk 439.25 from Tk 459.25. Square Pharma rose to Tk 3800 from Tk 3732.5 amid buying pressure. Of the other issues in turnover, Summit Power, DESCO, Pubali Bank, National Bank and Premier Bank traded upbeat. bd
